[[{"text": ["Python is strongly typed.", "There are no implicit type conversions."], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "strongly typed", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strong_typing"}]}, {"text": ["You have to do one of these:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"asd%d\" % 9\n\"asd\" + str(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}], [{"text": ["If it worked the way you expected it to (resulting in \"abc9\"), what would \"9\" + 9 deliver?", "18 or \"99\"?"], "childNum": 4, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "\"abc9\"", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}, {"text": "\"9\" + 9", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": -1, "childList": []}, {"text": "18", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 1, "childList": []}, {"text": "\"99\"", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["To remove this ambiguity, you are required to make explicit what you want to convert in this case:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abc\" + str(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}], [{"text": ["Either something like this:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abc\" + str(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}, {"text": ["or "], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abs{0}\".format(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 3}, {"text": ["or"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 4, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abs%d\" % (9,)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 5}], [{"text": ["Since Python is a strongly typed language, concatenating a string and an integer as you may do in Perl makes no sense, because there's no defined way to \"add\" strings and numbers to each other."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "Python is a strongly typed", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://wiki.python.org/moin/Why%20is%20Python%20a%20dynamic%20language%20and%20also%20a%20strongly%20typed%20language"}, {"text": "because there's no defined way to \"add\" strings and numbers to each other.", "childNum": 0, "tag": "em", "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["...says \"The Zen of Python\", so you have to concatenate two string objects.", "You can do this by creating a string from the integer using the built-in str() function:"], "childNum": 3, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "\"The Zen of Python\"", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0020/"}, {"text": "str()", "tag": "a", "pos": 1, "childList": [{"text": "str()", "tag": "code"}], "childNum": 1, "href": "http://docs.python.org/library/functions.html#str"}, {"text": "str()", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n &gt;&gt;&gt; \"abc\" + str(9)\n'abc9'\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}, {"text": ["Alternatively use Python's string formatting operations:"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 3, "childList": [{"text": "Python's string formatting operations", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://docs.python.org/library/stdtypes.html#string-formatting"}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n &gt;&gt;&gt; 'abc%d' % 9\n'abc9'\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 4}, {"text": ["Perhaps better still, use str.format():"], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 5, "childList": [{"text": "str.format()", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [{"text": "str.format()", "tag": "code"}], "childNum": 1, "href": "http://www.python.org/doc//current/library/stdtypes.html#str.format"}, {"text": "str.format()", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n &gt;&gt;&gt; 'abc{0}'.format(9)\n'abc9'\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 6}, {"text": ["The Zen also says:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 7, "childList": []}, {"text": ["Which is why I've given three options.", "It goes on to say..."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 8, "childList": []}], [{"text": ["You have to convert the int into a string:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abc\" + str(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}], [{"text": ["do it like this:"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n \"abc%s\" % 9\n#or\n\"abc\" + str(9)\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}]]